{
  "stem": "15962.7",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she was nursing us back to life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was liberated a little earlier.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She was also in Auschwitz and other camps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Her children were sent to the gas chamber the same day my father perished.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And her husband was killed in a-- air-- by-- by a bomb, by a British or American plane in-- in another concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] She took care of us, fed us, lodged us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she got a tutor for me because I haven't been to school for four years and I had a lot to catch up, and made it possible for me to take some exams and organize my acceptance to the high school, gymnasium in Nachod.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Since [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] she was-- her-- her house where she then lived was a-- a distance away from the school, we then agreed that during the week I would live with another couple, both of whom were survivors.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That was Rudolf and Wilma Beck, the person that I met in Auschwitz that I mentioned earlier.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They lost their son.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they were very interested in having me come and live with them and help me through these difficult times.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And, at first, I stayed there during the week, and Saturday afternoon, bicycled to Vera.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then Sunday evening or Monday morning, I would bicycle back into town.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Eventually, Vera [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] married another survivor, a doctor who lived in another town, and-- and moved away so that I lived permanently with the Becks in my hometown.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And that worked very well.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They were very sensitive and understanding.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And I [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] had a great deal to catch up and to learn in school, and struggled to keep my grades.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
